   "source": [
    "# Get started\n",
    "\n",
    "The following example shows the steps to develop a preventive maintenance policy\n",
    "by age on circuit breakers:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Perform a survival analysis on lifetime data,\n",
    "2. Compute the optimal age of replacement,\n",
    "3. Compute the expected total discounting costs and number of expected\n",
    "   replacements for the next years.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Survival analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "The survival analysis is perfomed by computing the Kaplan-Meier estimator and fitting the\n",
    "parameters of a Weibull and a Gompertz distribution with the maximum likelihood\n",
    "estimator."
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from relife2.utils.dataset import load_circuit_breaker\n",
    "\n",
    "time, event, entry = load_circuit_breaker()\n",
    "data = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    \"time\" : time,\n",
    "    \"event\" : event,\n",
    "    \"entry\" : entry\n",
    "})\n",
    "display(data.head(n=15))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "248798f5-f144-467b-a1a8-7d8b2e2d7b28",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from relife2 import KaplanMeier, Weibull, Gompertz\n",
    "\n",
    "km = KaplanMeier().fit(time,event,entry)\n",
    "weibull = Weibull().fit(time,event,entry)\n",
    "gompertz = Gompertz().fit(time,event,entry)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6a9fa74f-f7d7-45f2-92cc-aab3c8cd1026",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here are the estimated parameters after fitting the models (note that ``km`` does note have parameters as it is a non-parametric estimator)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "c2fd14b6-9493-4af8-b4f3-412b0b4fee36",
   "metadata": {},

     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Weibull parameters (shape, rate) :\", weibull.params)\n",
    "print(\"Gompertz parameters (shape, rate) :\", gompertz.params)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7a70dc80-a164-40ce-bb62-819a75baf362",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The results of fitting the Weibull and Gompertz distributions are compared by looking at their AIC. Those values are stored in the ``fitting_results`` instance created and saved inside your model instance after the fit."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "f6cd0b73-e950-4b54-8eb4-c162e1be62ff",
   "metadata": {},

      "Weibull AIC : 2493.721978543718\n",
      "Gompertz AIC : 2485.567310362761\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Weibull AIC :\", weibull.fitting_results.AIC)\n",
    "print(\"Gompertz AIC :\", gompertz.fitting_results.AIC)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e4022147-4a60-4bcb-be62-4fb92c13a513",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The Gompertz distribution gives the best fit and will be chosen for the next step of the study. The code below plots the survival function obtained by the Kaplan-Meier estimator and the maximum likelihood estimator for the Weibull and Gompertz distributions."
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "km.plot.sf()\n",
    "weibull.plot.sf()\n",
    "gompertz.plot.sf()\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Age [year]')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Survival probability')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c61d7149-edeb-4d0b-bab3-f6a26784d0e9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Optimal age replacement"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9b28708f-e9c6-45c2-b7bc-17902bfaf0d4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We consider 3 circuit breakers with the following parameters:\n",
    "\n",
    "- the current ages of the circuit breakers are 15, 20, and 25 years respectively\n",
    "- the preventive costs of replacement are evaluated 10 k€\n",
    "- the failure costs (e.g. lost energy) are evaluated 900, 500 and 100 k€ respectively\n",
    "- the discount rate is 0.04\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"alert alert-info\">\n",
    "When you want to pass different parameters for each asset, you generally encode them in a 2D array. The first axis corresponds to each assets and the second axis corresponds to the values.\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "Current ages are stored in ``a0``, preventive costs of replacement in ``cp``, failure costs in ``cf``. As there are three assets, we must reshape each array in 2D when necessary. "
   ]
  }
